# Quiz Creation Workflow

When creating a new quiz, follow this exact four-step process:

## Step 1: File Structure Setup

**Category and Naming:**
- Place quiz in relevant category folder (`sport/`, `gesetze/`, `ai/`) or create new category
- Use URL-friendly names: lowercase, short, underscores for multi-word names (e.g., `machine_learning`, `basketball`)

**Template Setup:**
```bash
# Create directory and copy template files
mkdir [category]/[quiz_name]
cp -r _template/copyme/* [category]/[quiz_name]/

# Update configuration
python update_config.py
```

## Step 2: Generate quiz.json

**Requirements:**
- Use provided source document (PDF) to generate questions
- Generate approximately 100 questions
- Structure must strictly adhere to `_template/schema.json`
- Each question must include:
  - 4 options (1 correct, 3 plausible distractors)
  - Brief explanation
  - Precise source citation (page, chapter)
  - Difficulty tag (`leicht`, `mittel`, or `schwer`)

**Validation:**
```bash
npx ajv validate -s _template/schema.json -d [category]/[quiz_name]/quiz.json
```

## Step 3: Create banner.png

**Design Requirements:**
- Dimensions: 1200x300px (4:1 ratio)
- Style: Modern, professional, align with app's primary color (`#546de5`)
- Content: Thematic illustration without text
- Location: Save as `banner.png` inside quiz directory

## Step 4: Customize index.html

**Required Changes:**

**Page Title:**
```html
<title>[Quiz Name] Quiz</title>
```

**Favicon:**
```html
<link rel="icon" href="data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 100 100'><text y='.9em' font-size='90'>[EMOJI]</text></svg>">
```

**Loading Animation:**
```html
<div id="loading">
  <div class="loading-spinner">[EMOJI]</div>
  <p>[Quiz Name] Quiz wird geladen...</p>
</div>
```